sentence: > Yes that's what is said in the DrawClone documentation. But what about using simply Draw instead of DrawClone in these examples ?. sentence: DrawClone also create a new object object see line 225 [here](https://root.cern/doc/master/TObject_8cxx_source.html#l00219) . The problem with DrawClone is that it will go in the SelectedPad, not in the Pad define by cd()... They may coincide sometime but not always. So, I think it is better to make it clear a Clone is needed to avoir deletion. Then this object is drawn ... but the primary thing is to avoid deletion.
